HEADWORD: load-shedding
<hw>load-shedding</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of
disconnecting the electric current on certain lines when the demand
becomes greater than the supply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

